                <li>Critical analysis of arguments (2 slides)</li>
                <li>Recommendations with justification (2 slides)</li>
            </ul>
            <p><strong>Requirements:</strong> Visual data representation, credible sources, acknowledgment of limitations</p>
        </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="assessment-option">
        <h4>Option 3: Live Debate Contribution (45 minutes total)</h4>
        <div class="digital-option">
            <p><strong>Format:</strong> Structured class debate with prepared position</p>
            <p><strong>Preparation:</strong></p>
            <ul>
                <li>Research brief (written, 300 words)</li>
                <li>Opening argument (2 minutes spoken)</li>
                <li>Response to counter-arguments (throughout debate)</li>
                <li>Closing synthesis (1 minute)</li>
            </ul>
            <p><strong>Requirements:</strong> Evidence-based arguments, respectful engagement, acknowledgment of complexity</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="student-activity">
    <h3>üîç Research & Analysis Phase <span class="timing">25 minutes in-class + homework</span></h3>
    
    <div class="challenge-phase">
        <h4>Phase 1: Source Investigation (10 minutes)</h4>
        <ul>
            <li>Identify 4+ credible sources from different perspectives</li>
            <li>Use fact-checking tools (Google Fact Check Explorer, Snopes)</li>
            <li>Evaluate source bias and reliability</li>
            <li>Document sources using provided template</li>
        </ul>
        
        <p><strong>Required Source Types:</strong></p>
        <ul>
            <li>Government/official data (stats.govt.nz, ministry websites)</li>
            <li>Academic research or expert analysis</li>
            <li>News reporting from reputable outlets</li>
            <li>Community/iwi perspectives (where relevant)</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
    
    <div class="challenge-phase">
        <h4>Phase 2: Critical Analysis (15 minutes)</h4>
        <ul>
            <li>Identify key stakeholders and their interests</li>
            <li>Map arguments for/against different positions</li>
            <li>Evaluate evidence quality and identify gaps</li>
            <li>Consider cultural dimensions and Te Ao MƒÅori perspectives</li>
        </ul>
        
        <p><strong>Analysis Framework:</strong></p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Evidence Evaluation:</strong> Is this fact, opinion, or interpretation?</li>
            <li><strong>Bias Detection:</strong> What interests might influence this perspective?</li>
            <li><strong>Logical Structure:</strong> Do the conclusions follow from the premises?</li>
            <li><strong>Missing Voices:</strong> Whose perspectives are not represented?</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
    
    <p><strong>Homework Component:</strong> Complete research and prepare chosen assessment format (estimated 60-90 minutes)</p>
</div>

<div class="student-activity">
