    <h3>üéØ Differentiation & Support Strategies</h3>
    
    <h4>For Advanced Learners:</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>Challenge to analyze international comparisons or policy alternatives</li>
        <li>Require synthesis of 6+ sources from diverse perspectives</li>
        <li>Ask them to propose original solutions or compromises</li>
        <li>Encourage exploration of underlying philosophical or ethical frameworks</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h4>For Developing Learners:</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>Provide pre-selected, vetted sources to analyze</li>
        <li>Offer templates for argument structure and analysis</li>
        <li>Allow collaborative partnerships for research and preparation</li>
        <li>Break assessment into smaller, scaffolded steps</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h4>For ESL/Language Support:</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>Provide key vocabulary glossaries</li>
        <li>Allow extra time for research and preparation</li>
        <li>Offer sentence starters and paragraph templates</li>
        <li>Consider allowing presentation in Te Reo MƒÅori where appropriate</li>
    </ul>
</div>

